.TH DUPLEX 1 "March 2026" "duplex 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
duplex \- manual duplex printing for non-duplex printers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B duplex
.RI [ input.pdf ]
.RI [ "lpr options" ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B duplex
is a shell script that enables manual duplex (two-sided) printing on printers
that do not support automatic duplex. It splits a PDF into even and odd pages,
prints the even pages first, then prompts the user to flip and reload the paper
before printing the odd pages on the reverse side.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I input.pdf
The PDF file to print. If omitted or set to "\-", reads from standard input.
.TP
.I "lpr options"
Any additional options are passed directly to
.BR lpr (1).
.SH USAGE
.IP 1. 4
Run \fBduplex\fR with your PDF file.
.IP 2. 4
The script prints even-numbered pages first.
.IP 3. 4
When prompted, remove the printed pages from the output tray.
.IP 4. 4
Flip the stack and place it in Tray 1 with the printed side facing up.
.IP 5. 4
Press Enter to print the odd-numbered pages on the reverse side.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The printer name is hardcoded in the script as
.BR Hewlett-Packard_HP_Color_LaserJet_M553 .
Edit the script to change the \fBP\fR variable for your printer.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.BR pdftk (1)
Used to split the PDF into even and odd pages.
.TP
.BR lpr (1)
Used to send print jobs to the printer (provided by CUPS).
.SH FILES
The script creates temporary PDF files in \fB/tmp\fR which are automatically
cleaned up on exit or when interrupted.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful completion.
.TP
.B >0
An error occurred.
.SH EXAMPLES
Print a PDF file:
.RS
.nf
duplex document.pdf
.fi
.RE
.PP
Print from a pipeline:
.RS
.nf
cat document.pdf | duplex
.fi
.RE
.PP
Print with additional lpr options:
.RS
.nf
duplex document.pdf -o media=letter
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lpr (1),
.BR pdftk (1),
.BR cups (1)
